commit.message:
Prepare for the next release

[skip ci]

CI(Travis): Install `typing` for Python 3.4

`auditwheel` requires `typing`
but `typing` became a module in stdlib
only in Python 3.5.
Style: Fix flake8 E741 ambiguous variable name 'l'

Docs(news): Improve formatting.

Remove uninteresting news item.

[skip ci]
CI(Travis): Run tests under Python 3.8 on MacOS

Build(devscripts): Fix `release`

Repair all linux wheels, 32- and 64-bit.
Use python3.6 to run `auditwheel` for Python 2.7 wheels.

[skip ci]

Build: Install `wheel` and `auditwheel` that correspond to each other

`wheel==0.34.1` and `auditwheel==3.1.0`.

CI(AppVeyor): Downgrade `pip` from vendored archives for Python 3.4

Downgrade `pip`/`pkg_resources`/`setuptools` to work around a bug in tox
that upgrades packages too eagerly and installs incompatible versions.

Build(devscripts): Pre-releases must be released from `master`

[skip ci]

Docs(news): Limit dependencies versions for Python 2.7

[skip ci]

Docs(news): Document how to use new `extras_require`

[skip ci]

Build(setup.py): Add extra `markdown` as an alias for `filters

[skip ci]
Setup: add markdown as an optional dependency
